There is no `express.json()` or `express.urlencoded()` middleware. When someone adds a POST route, they will bolt it on and may omit size limits, opening a JSON/body-bomb DoS vector.

**Fix — add body parsing with explicit size caps now:**

```js
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));        // reject oversized JSON bodies
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false, limit: '10kb' }));
```

