### 7. No Global Error Handler — Stack Traces Leaked (OWASP A05)

Without an error-handling middleware, unhandled errors fall through to Express's default handler, which sends the stack trace in the response body in development *and* can do so accidentally in production.

**Fix — add a catch-all error handler as the last middleware:**

```js
// Must have exactly 4 parameters so Express recognises it as an error handler
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  // Log full error internally
  console.error({ err, url: req.url, method: req.method });

  // Never expose internals to the client
  const statusCode = err.status ?? err.statusCode ?? 500;
  res.status(statusCode).json({
    error: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'
      ? 'Internal server error'
      : err.message,
  });
});
```

