**Framework:** Express.js

The app is intentionally minimal, but that makes it a useful baseline for demonstrating how quickly a small Express service accumulates risk. Below are findings mapped to OWASP Top 10 (2021) categories, ordered by severity.

---

## Summary Table

| # | Finding | Severity | OWASP Category |
|---|---------|----------|----------------|
| 1 | No authentication on `/users` | 🔴 Critical | A01 – Broken Access Control |
| 2 | Secrets committed to repository | 🔴 Critical | A02 – Cryptographic/Secrets Failures |
| 3 | Missing security headers (no Helmet) | 🟠 High | A05 – Security Misconfiguration |
| 4 | No input validation | 🟠 High | A03 – Injection |
| 5 | No rate limiting | 🟠 High | A04 – Insecure Design |
